{"image_id": "CINF_2012_page_76", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2012 10-K - 74", "bbox": [401.3, 1600.4, 780.9, 1622.7]}, {"text": "EXCESS AND SURPLUS LINES INSURANCE RESULTS OF OPERATIONS", "bbox": [90.0, 57.0, 896.8, 96.0]}, {"text": "Overview – Three-Year Highlights", "bbox": [90.0, 97.5, 495.7, 132.1]}, {"text": "Our excess and surplus lines segment includes results of The Cincinnati Specialty Underwriters Insurance", "bbox": [90.0, 722.9, 1071.7, 750.5]}, {"text": "Company and CSU Producer Resources Inc. The year 2012 represented our fifth full year of operations for", "bbox": [90.0, 746.9, 1077.4, 774.5]}, {"text": "our excess and surplus lines segment. Performance highlights for the excess and surplus lines", "bbox": [90.0, 770.9, 966.6, 798.5]}, {"text": "segment include:", "bbox": [90.0, 794.7, 259.0, 822.3]}, {"text": "•", "bbox": [90.0, 826.4, 105.3, 854.0]}, {"text": "Premiums – Earned premiums continued to climb in 2012, a result of strong growth in net written", "bbox": [127.5, 826.4, 1021.0, 854.0]}, {"text": "premiums, similar to 2011. Growth of net written premiums in 2012 was driven by higher renewal written", "bbox": [127.5, 850.4, 1088.9, 878.0]}, {"text": "premiums that included rising average renewal price increases. New business written premiums for", "bbox": [127.5, 874.4, 1045.5, 902.0]}, {"text": "2012 rose compared with 2011, reflecting higher pricing in an excess and surplus lines market that", "bbox": [127.5, 898.2, 1039.7, 925.8]}, {"text": "continued to experience strong competition.", "bbox": [127.5, 922.2, 536.5, 949.8]}, {"text": "•", "bbox": [90.0, 953.9, 105.2, 981.5]}, {"text": "Combined ratio – The combined ratio rose 8.8 percentage points in 2012, primarily due to unusually", "bbox": [127.5, 953.9, 1050.2, 981.5]}, {"text": "large net favorable reserve development on prior accident years during 2011. Most of this increase was", "bbox": [127.4, 977.7, 1083.9, 1005.3]}, {"text": "from higher loss expenses. The loss ratio component rose 2.5 points, including 1.3 points from higher", "bbox": [127.4, 1001.7, 1065.1, 1029.3]}, {"text": "large losses, as shown on the Excess and Surplus Lines Insurance Losses by Size table on Page 76.", "bbox": [127.4, 1025.7, 1065.4, 1053.3]}, {"text": "Excess and Surplus Lines Insurance Premiums", "bbox": [90.0, 1055.3, 659.5, 1089.9]}, {"text": "The $24 million increase in 2012 renewal premiums reflected the opportunity to renew many policies for the", "bbox": [90.0, 1275.1, 1082.9, 1302.7]}, {"text": "first time as well as higher renewal pricing. Average renewal pricing rose in the high-single-digit range", "bbox": [90.0, 1299.1, 1030.2, 1326.8]}, {"text": "during each quarter of 2012, improving over the mid-single-digit range for the last quarter of 2011. We", "bbox": [90.0, 1323.1, 1032.8, 1350.8]}, {"text": "measure average changes in excess and surplus lines renewal pricing as the rate of change in renewal", "bbox": [90.0, 1347.2, 1044.9, 1374.8]}, {"text": "premium for the new policy period compared with the premium for the expiring policy period, assuming no", "bbox": [90.0, 1371.2, 1066.7, 1398.8]}, {"text": "change in the level of insured exposures or policy coverage between those periods for respective policies.", "bbox": [90.0, 1395.2, 1076.8, 1422.8]}, {"text": "New business written premiums for the year 2012 rose 9 percent, compared with 2011, primarily due to", "bbox": [90.0, 1425.2, 1044.7, 1452.8]}, {"text": "higher pricing as the excess and surplus lines market remained competitive, including activity by standard", "bbox": [90.0, 1449.2, 1066.7, 1476.8]}, {"text": "market companies writing policies for risks formerly insurable only in the excess and surplus lines market.", "bbox": [90.0, 1473.2, 1065.7, 1500.8]}, {"text": "We observed many cases where competing carriers offered policy terms and conditions that were less", "bbox": [90.0, 1497.2, 1037.0, 1524.8]}, {"text": "restrictive than those we observed in the past for similar risks, without a corresponding premium for the", "bbox": [90.0, 1521.2, 1042.5, 1548.8]}, {"text": "broadened insurance coverage. Therefore, we declined to write many of those new business opportunities", "bbox": [90.0, 1545.2, 1072.9, 1572.8]}, {"text": "and also some renewal business opportunities.", "bbox": [90.0, 1569.0, 529.0, 1596.6]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [36.6, 135.5, 147.1, 153.3]}, {"text": "2012-2011", "bbox": [866.5, 134.3, 940.1, 156.8]}, {"text": "2011-2010", "bbox": [981.2, 134.7, 1054.6, 156.8]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [498.4, 154.8, 532.4, 177.2]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [627.5, 155.5, 661.5, 177.6]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [756.6, 155.5, 790.6, 177.6]}, {"text": "Change %", "bbox": [865.3, 155.2, 941.7, 177.6]}, {"text": "Change %", "bbox": [983.2, 155.5, 1052.6, 177.6]}, {"text": "Earned premiums", "bbox": [37.0, 184.9, 155.8, 207.0]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [454.7, 185.2, 463.1, 207.6]}, {"text": "93", "bbox": [539.6, 185.2, 556.5, 207.6]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [583.8, 185.1, 592.2, 207.2]}, {"text": "70", "bbox": [668.7, 185.1, 685.6, 207.2]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [712.9, 185.1, 721.3, 207.2]}, {"text": "49", "bbox": [797.8, 185.1, 814.7, 207.2]}, {"text": "33", "bbox": [912.9, 185.2, 929.8, 207.6]}, {"text": "43", "bbox": [1027.4, 185.1, 1044.3, 207.2]}, {"text": "Loss and loss expenses from:", "bbox": [37.0, 213.1, 233.8, 235.2]}, {"text": "Current accident year before catastrophe losses", "bbox": [37.0, 234.0, 375.9, 256.1]}, {"text": "68", "bbox": [539.6, 234.3, 556.5, 256.7]}, {"text": "50", "bbox": [668.7, 234.2, 685.6, 256.3]}, {"text": "41", "bbox": [797.8, 234.2, 814.7, 256.3]}, {"text": "36", "bbox": [912.9, 234.3, 929.8, 256.7]}, {"text": "22", "bbox": [1027.4, 234.2, 1044.3, 256.3]}, {"text": "Current accident year catastrophe losses", "bbox": [37.0, 254.9, 328.5, 277.0]}, {"text": "2", "bbox": [548.1, 255.1, 556.5, 277.6]}, {"text": "1", "bbox": [677.2, 255.1, 685.6, 